</li><li id="tree_64678864" class="comment full contain"><span class="ind"></span>
<div id="comment_status_64678864" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64678864" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64678864" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_64678864" name="comment_link_64678864" href="//yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23410446&amp;cid=64678864" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64678864)" >Apple cannot track you this way</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64678864" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64678864); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>5</a>, Informative)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~EMB+Numbers">EMB Numbers</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~EMB+Numbers">( 934125 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64678864">		
		on Saturday August 03, 2024 @08:46PM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23410446&amp;cid=64678864">#64678864</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64678864"><p>A) Apple cannot track you this way. A cryptographic signature that is generated on your device is used. Apple has no access to the signature.<br>B) When a device is factory reset, cryptographic keys are regenerated, and it becomes impossible to track the device via "find my". Used devices are not a "find my" privacy issue for this among many other reasons.<br>C) If you don't like it, turn it off, and it is really off. This is in contrast to Goole who continued to track Android phone locations even when opt out.  <a href="https://www.tomsguide.com/news/android-phones-track-you-even-when-you-opt-out-new-research-reveals" title="tomsguide.com">https://www.tomsguide.com/news...</a> [tomsguide.com].</p><p>One company makes money by invading your privacy, and it isn't Apple.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64678864">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_64678864" class="btn link" href="//yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23410446&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=64678864" onclick="D2.replyTo(64678864); return false;">Reply to This</a> <span class="ind"></span><a class="btn link" rel="nofollow" href="//yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23410446&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;cid=64678840" onclick="return D2.selectParent(64678840)">Parent</a> 	<a rel="nofollow" href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
